body.description: Get the superior performance and softness you’ve been waiting for with Cottonelle GentlePlus Flushable Wet Wipes with Aloe & Vitamin E, designed to leave you comfortably dry. The extra soft cleaning ripples are safe for sensitive skin and clean gently while removing moisture. Cottonelle is septic-safe and clog-free. Each pack has 42 flushable wet wipes per pack so you can worry less about running out when you or guests at your home need it most. Looking for more ways to feel clean down there after taking care of business? Use Cottonelle toilet paper to feel shower fresh. Conveniently remain stocked on flushable wipes by ordering Cottonelle for delivery to your door or pickup curbside. Cottonelle cares about you and our planet. We are proud to be FSC certified ensuring the forests we source from are responsibly managed to prevent deforestation and help protect the trees and animals that depend on them. We also use fibers that are 100% plant-based and no harsh chemicals or dyes.

What are Cottonelle Flushable Wipes and why should I use them? Cottonelle Flushable Wipes are plastic-free and alcohol-free wet wipes that are flushable in toilets. Flushable wipes give you a refreshing clean that you can’t get by using toilet paper alone. Cottonelle Flushable Wipes are convenient for travel. Is it safe to flush Cottonelle Flushable Wipes? Yes. Cottonelle Flushable Wipes are tested with plumbers, pass widely accepted flushability guidelines. Our wipes are designed to safely break down in well-maintained sewage systems and home septic systems. Are baby wipes flushable? No. Baby wipes include plastic and are designed to deliver durability and value. Why do some plumbers say not to flush wipes? Many plumbers aren’t aware that there are different types of wipes. Cottonelle Flushable Wipes are tested with plumbers and meet all flushability guidelines. Are Cottonelle Flushable Wipes sustainably made? Yes. Cottonelle Flushable Wipes are made of tree pulp from responsibly managed forests. Cottonelle packaging that features the FSC label states that product was made in a way that promotes sustainability.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 3, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Works well does the job. Best price for the quantity. Soft and clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 24, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Seam to Break Down Well
reviews.reviewText: I like these wipes a lot. I've experimented with them along with other brands to see which ones break up in water the best and I was pleased with these. The feel is nice and gentle. You do have to be careful when taking them out of the package because they can tear. I personally feel better flushing these than others but you will have to judge that for yourself. I like ordering them in the box from Amazon because in the stores they are stuck together with some type of sticky banding material that I I don't enjoy dealing with.
